reviews.review_text:
Sounds Fantastic! This source sounds pretty damn amazing.  Clear, upfront sound from the OTS.  Amazingly nice bass too.  

There's a little bit of panning or adjustment happening during Iko, but it's all good :)

Thank goodness cassettes can be converted to digital with such accurate reproduction these days.  Kudos to both Keith (the taper) and M. Watson for a killer transfer job.

holy shit! built to last hopefully you have yourself a pair of nice studio monitors to enjoy this one.  work yourself up a nice buzz, crank this fucker up and dance your ass off to the real deal rock n' roll.  jerry is alive and kickin' by the second solo on aiko aiko he nails it and his vocals will give you chills down your spine!!  yet another example of how an audience recording far surpasses a soundboard.

SBD In my honest opinion this is Not an Audience.

it sounds nothing like the other recordings made with the same mics during similar years.

Needs source correction.
---------
nice crazy fingers though

Boards...? ...WE DON' NEED NO STINKIN' BOARDS!!!

I did rate this at five stars, but I'm taking one off because it's almost a semitone fast - I'd say about 40 cents, for those who know digital editing geek speak.  If Watson could do a pitch fix on this it'd be greatly appreciated.  Then I can feel comfortable adding it to the "pristine" section of gdluckynumbers.org.  Thanks.
MATRIX or SBD This is a wonderful performance from a year that is filled with grate shows.No way this is an AUD though.sounds like a well mixed Matrix

this IS an audience recording guys, no need to go all conspiracy theory here.  I can 100% vouch that this is my AUDIENCE master from this show made with my Sennheiser ME-80's, this is NOT a SBD nor any type of matrix.
